#### **6. Notification Service** ğŸ”” **MEDIUM PRIORITY**
**Why useful:** Central notification management
- Push notifications (mobile/web)
- SMS notifications
- Email notifications (complements email MS)
- In-app notifications
- Multi-channel preference management

**Usage:** Business services trigger notifications via this

#### **7. File Storage Service** ğŸ“ **MEDIUM PRIORITY**
**Why valuable:** Centralized file management
- Image upload and processing
- Document storage
- File transformation (resize, optimize)
- CDN integration
- Access control and permissions

**Usage:** Any service needing file handling

#### **8. Search Service** ğŸ” **MEDIUM PRIORITY**
**Why important:** Enterprise search capability
- Full-text search across all content
- Faceted search and filtering
- Auto-complete and suggestions
- Search analytics
- Index management

**Usage:** Content-heavy applications

#### **9. Logging & Monitoring** ğŸ“ˆ **LOWER PRIORITY** (if you have external tools)
**Why useful:** Centralized observability
- Application logs aggregation
- Performance metrics
- Error tracking and alerting
- Health checks across all services
- Distributed tracing

**Note:** May use external tools like DataDog, New Relic instead

